                <h1>USCIS Background Checks: What Petitioners Need to Know</h1>
                <p>Yes, USCIS conducts background checks on petitioners to ensure the integrity of the immigration process. This includes reviewing criminal history, immigration status, and other relevant information to assess the petitioner’s eligibility and qualifications. Such checks help protect national security and uphold U.S. immigration laws.</p>
